Package: leghist
Type: Package
Title: Automated legislative history analysis for R
Version: 0.1
Date: 2012-05-30
Author: Mark Huberty and Hillary Sanders
Maintainer: Mark Huberty <markhuberty@berkeley.edu>
Description: Provides facilities for using natural language tools in R for the
    analysis of legislative texts, mapping the progress of legislative
    amendments and other document changes through the legislative process,
    modeling the content of bills and proposed changes, and visualizing
    legislative flow.
Depends: tm, topicmodels, stringr, lsa, RWeka, Matrix, gdata, Hmisc, reshape, plyr
License: Simplified BSD
Collate:
    'leg_functions.R'
